ported issues. The existing test covers dynamic loading, so modifying a second test to use `StaticMappedBean.class` could help clarify things further.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining class references**\\n\\nI’m considering that the `className` includes the test class `$StaticMappedBean`, which will return after the first failure. This should trigger line 501 and call `getMethod`. Since the class reference is a `WeakReference(null)`, we won’t need a dynamic definition, and this approach should run natively, which could help avoid the dynamic catch issue. I’m thinking about making `StaticMappedBean` a public nested class. Inner classes can have the `$` in their names, but it seems top-level public classes shouldn’t, so there’s some clarification needed there.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PIFiHMOAyQEpUUwA28b0CSbd|fc_09747e8140c424bf0169f4e4efec38819e992210d911a41354", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    void reconstructsMappedMethodWhenFirstContextClassLoaderReloadAttemptFails() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            IsolatedMappedBeanClassLoader classLoader = new IsolatedMappedBeanClassLoader(\n                    MappedPropertyDescriptorInnerMappedMethodReferenceTest.class.getClassLoader()\n            );\n            Class<?> beanClass = classLoader.loadClass(MAPPED_BEAN_CLASS);\n            MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor = new MappedPropertyDescriptor(\"values\", beanClass);\n            FailsOnceMappedBeanClassLoader failsOnceClassLoader = new FailsOnceMappedBeanClassLoader(beanClass);\n\n            clearCachedMethodAndClass(descriptor, \"mappedReadMethodRef\");\n\n            ClassLoader previousContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n            try {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(failsOnceClassLoader);\n\n                Method readMethod = descriptor.getMappedReadMethod();\n\n                assertThat(readMethod.getName()).isEqualTo(\"getValues\");\n                assertThat(readMethod.getDeclaringClass()).isSameAs(beanClass);\n                assertThat(failsOnceClassLoader.loadAttempts()).isEqualTo(2);\n            } finally {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousContextClassLoader);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    void reconstructsMappedMethodWhenFirstContextClassLoaderReloadAttemptFails() throws Exception {\n        MappedPropertyDescriptor descriptor = new MappedPropertyDescriptor(\"values\", StaticMappedBean.class);\n        FailsOnceMappedBeanClassLoader failsOnceClassLoader = new FailsOnceMappedBeanClassLoader(StaticMappedBean.class);\n\n        clearCachedMethodAndClass(descriptor, \"mappedReadMethodRef\");\n\n        ClassLoader previousContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(failsOnceClassLoader);\n\n            Method readMethod = descriptor.getMappedReadMethod();\n\n            assertThat(readMethod.getName()).isEqualTo(\"getValues\");\n            assertThat(readMethod.getDeclaringClass()).isSameAs(StaticMappedBean.class);\n            assertThat(failsOnceClassLoader.loadAttempts()).isEqualTo(2);\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2153, "output": 1414, "cacheRead": 60928, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 64495, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "t